data: {"type":"response.output_text.done","content_index":0,"item_id":"msg_082c3a955c8ddbff0069a2888cd1388197bc5b9b66b1d153a0","logprobs":[],"output_index":2,"sequence_number":493,"text":"Foundry Agent Service is the **runtime layer in Microsoft Foundry** for building, deploying, and operating **production-ready AI agents** (not just chatbots). It’s designed to help you move from prototypes to reliable, governed agentic apps by handling orchestration, tool use, and “ops” concerns for you.【5:0†source】\n\n### What it does\n- **Runs and manages agent conversations and sessions** (threads/runs) and coordinates multi-step agent execution.【5:0†source】\n- **Orchestrates tool calls** so the model can decide when to fetch knowledge or take actions (and then use the results to respond).【5:0†source】\n- **Applies trust/safety and governance** as part of the runtime (for example, policy enforcement and content safety as the agent operates).【5:0†source】\n- **Integrates with enterprise infrastructure** such as identity, networking, and observability so agents can be operated securely at scale.【5:0†source】\n\n### Tools (how agents get real work done)\nFoundry Agent Service supports a catalog of built-in and integratable tools, generally in two buckets【5:1†source】:\n\n**Knowledge tools** (ground responses in data):\n- Azure AI Search, file search, Fabric, etc.\n- Public web grounding (for real-time info) via Bing-based tools【5:1†source】\n\n**Action tools** (do things / automate workflows):\n- Azure Logic Apps, OpenAPI-based tools, MCP endpoints, function calling, Azure Functions, browser automation, and more【5:1†source】\n\n### Web grounding options (common example)\n- **Grounding with Bing Search**: lets an agent pull **real-time public web data** and return answers with citations (users don’t get raw search chunks).【5:2†source】\n- **Grounding with Bing Custom Search**: similar, but you can restrict search to a **configured set of domains/subdomains** so results come only from sources you choose.【5:3†source】\n\n### When you’d use it\nUse Foundry Agent Service when you want an agent that can:\n- Answer questions using your data + web data (grounded responses),\n- Execute multi-step workflows (tickets, invoicing, content publishing, internal ops),\n- Be deployed with enterprise-grade controls and monitoring rather than “demo chatbot” behavior.【5:0†source】\n\nIf you tell me what you’re building (support agent, internal knowledge agent, workflow automation, etc.), I can suggest a typical architecture (tools + data sources + deployment approach) in Foundry."}

